caption: Came here for a Saturday morning coffee with a friend. We both ordered the Croissants (Almond and Chocolate). The croissants were nice and crispy on the outside and fluffy on the inside. I honestly cannot say enough good things about these …
Great place with a wonderful staff, yesterday before close the man who helped up (presumably the owner) was so kind and quick to make sure everything was wonderful. Will be back for sure
This is the best pastry. So fresh

Best patisserie cafe in west Los Angeles. I had the german chocolate cake with my coffee and the atmosphere was great. Staff was super friendly and professional. I highly recommend anyone who has a sweet tooth. Come here for yummy desserts and treat yourself your deserve it.

First visit here although I've driven by many times. I only had coffee and thought it was great. Didn't try the food although the wraps and sandwiches looked good as well It's a great spot for a meeting or just hang out with friends. The clientele seems mostly hipster and same goes for the staff. But I have no problem with that.
Fabulous place. Servers can be condescending, but their top notch food and drinks keep you coming back.
I'm addicted to my iced honey oat latte. Also can't stop ordering my avocado toast without the spread and  I add a soft scramble. Consistently my favorite go to. Yummmm.

The place is total hipsterville. The do offer a decent breakfast, loud music, and outside seating. I had the Protein Plate which was pretty good. My only gripe is that they serve the food in carton boxes. It is not my preference to eat out of a carton box. Overall, decent food and coffee.
Great coffee. Had the Gibraltar. It was perfect. Latte art was dope too (always little bonus). Would've like to stay to try the espresso straight up and some food, but had to run catch a flight.

This place is absolutely one of the best place in the neighborhood. Every time I come there I am so pleased. They keep their high  level service and the topmost level of dishes  they provide. You are always happy with this place. Warmly  recommended.

Thank you #portosbakery. I recommend the "we make, you bake". Everything came out delicious and perfect for our brunch. The delivery was seemless, the instructions quick and easy.  We were able to serve fresh hot cheese rolls and guava cheese pastries in Sugarloaf, Ca. We cannot wait to order again.
Amazing pastry

I am a big fan of Emili’s pastry’s and have been for sometime. The food and pastries are always fresh, and the coffee is superb. It’s also nice to know that this is a locally run and operated business. I especially love their princess …

I love everything about this place. Prior to lockdowns, you could find me sipping a morning coffee and danish, and now w covid I go back and order their amazing cakes often. I usually buy a cake for all of my family events. During covid, …

This place has artists which serve ice cream.  You pick your flavor, your animal and let your artist do his thing.  When he comes back, you have a delightfully cute ice cream cone that brings happiness to you visually and taste-wise.  If you get multiple scoops, they draw animals on all your scoops and its just so cute and fun.

Yesterday was our first time we went to this place. But It is definitely not the last. We had a good time with the courteous service, with the exceptional  dishes and booze and with the decent charge. We will surely return there again.

I come here a lot. Cake and pastry very good. Patty who I think is the manager, is very nice and helpful. Today however I bought a chocolate mousse for a little gift and they are apparently now using styrofoam for a single slice instead of …

Had the best experience here last week! My husband is from Sweden and I was searching high and low for a princess cake! The almond marzipan, cream and the jam are his favorite, he said that this princess cake here was actually the best one …
Best banana pudding in LA. I've had different varieties and enjoy all of them.
got another cake from them. this place is magical. had to drive from glendale to get it but everybody loved it. absolutely the most moist and delicious cake. do try their strawberry cake.
Had this fire cake. Was In the rush to get a birthday cake for my uncle, not only did I get my cake in 2 minutes but this cake is fuego. Kuddos to my guy Jason, see you soon!
Best bakery for treatos
My favorite bakery! Everything is fresh and delicious. I love to go for a coffee and pastry. Desert from Emil’s makes every occasion that much more special!

Super cute cafe with an amazing selection of baked goods! Any European must visit for a chance to feel at home
I love their Blackforest, authentic!

Love the pastries, especially the apple strudel. Belong to the rewards club, but I am only in LA on occasion for family. Received my birthday text offer, but I wasn’t in town at the time. It expired on the 11th and wasn’t honored on the 14th when I went in to pick up the strudel I ordered yesterday. A bit disappointing.
We love the quality food, great service and quaint atmosphere of Emil's.
Love this place! Tropical green is my favorite but all of the smoothies I have tried have been great. Good customer service as well .
This bakery really does live up to its hype. Grab a pain Au chocolate and head to Mission Emil's Patisserie and Cafe Park to inhale and dog-watch.

Sent me back to sitting in a Paris Bistro. Very good homely food. It really doesn't try to be anything other than good French food. Very calm ambiance and their waiter Francisco was very welcoming. Will definetely be coming back!

What a cute little French restaurant, and what a real pleasant surprise! I literally live 1 minute 1/2 walking distance from it.. I am French, and I walked by a gazillion times without even thinking of giving it a try!! Well, tonight, I gave it a try!
The Church of 8 Wheels now offers lessons on Saturdays with certified skate instructors! Perfect for getting a boost on your roller skills.
The banana pudding was to die for. I am glad I live an hour or two away, because I would be significantly larger around the waist!

Great neighborhood establishment! My biggest complaint is that they are closed Mondays! The staff is very consistent and super friendly. They do a wonderful job decorating for the holidays as well. I find the decor simple, cozy and …
Their cakes was presented nicely and it's so delicious. Good place to buy cakes for special occasions.

The best cannoli of all time better than anything I’ve ever tried in any category. Lovely service, incredibly cute homey atmosphere,  impossibly delicious pastries with a massive, freshly baked variety.

I’ve been coming here for the past month and I love the pastries and cakes. They are great for someone with a sweet tooth but I must say the staff could be a little friendlier. It always feels like they give you an attitude.
Delicious, although I wish more prices were marked. Menu doesn't say it but coffee comes with one free refill.
Absolutely wonderful!! Not only was the service great but the cake was DELICIOUS. It was the hit of the party!! THANK YOU! I will be back soon.
Excellent service and food in a very hip setting.
Delicious, not cheap but that's ok. Quiet spot to read, browse or chat with loved ones.

Great service, EXCELENT cake, awesome atmosphere for small, intimate meetings.
I love their vegan banana bread! The people there are always willing to offer their best. Thanks for the hospitality.
Love this place, the pastries are excellent and the ambience is nice. Perfect to relax on the weekend.

2:30 pm on a Friday and the line is out the door for good reason! The baked goods are outstanding - croissants, chocolate croissants and morning buns were on my purchase list. I was sorry to miss their kouign amann, which I hear is wonderful. I'll definitely go back to try more!
dirty tables, too salty quiche
delicious sandwiches and pastries
Great service and wonderful pastries!
My favorite remote work spot.

Great quiches and coffee for a quick bite n smite. Eat a quiche, sip on some iced americanos, and plot the demise of your foes. Quiches are fluffy, my favorite is the Alpen, ham sandwich is good, never had the pastries but I assume they are good. The staff are lovely and will always give a sincere smile too :)
Reasonably priced
Tried the Black Forest cake and cheese apricot danish and figure 8 delicious chocolate is perfect. It's quiet calm and clean, the employee are awesome patient and friendly
Love the quiche!
Very good coffee. Funny to listen to German radio in this part of town.

The princess cake was the best I've had in L. A.  The elements are hard to perfect and they did a great job, especially the perfectly thin .  flavorful and masterfully placed almond fondant. Very good and easy service.  Parking int he building may be avail, but that is not clear.

Very nice display cabinet.  Tried the wedding cookies, molasses raisin cookie and a twist.  The molass cookie was very tasty.  The others were ok. The service was was slow.  Oh, the bags are noisy if you are getting your treats for the …
Got to try 3 different cakes and they were all delicious. Would recommend this place to anyone.
Very good cakes, great selection of aweets and pastries, friendly aervice.
Love everything about Emil's. One of my favorite coffee, pastries, and cake spots in LA. Great customer service too.
Wonderful coffee and tea, always with exceptional service, these ladies are so sweet!

Their cream puffs had a bland gelatine textured custard filling that I'm not a fan of. That said nearly everything else I've had I have loved. Their cookies and cakes are great. The princess cake is a surprising favorite.

Emil's is my FAVORITE bakery in West Los Angeles.  It definitely reminds me of a classic European cafe - no rush to get you in and out, quality food and a welcoming, relaxing atmosphere.  They make fruit tarts, a whole slew of amazing cookies and pastries and wonderful coffee.
Ok coffee, but the cakes and pastries are out of this world.
